          "body": "Four times in vv. 5-7 the text says of the beast: *it was given to him* (Greek *edothē*) — a mouth speaking great things (v. 5a), authority to act forty-two months (v. 5b), authority to make war on the saints (v. 7a), authority over every tribe and tongue (v. 7b). The grammatical agent is suppressed, but in apocalyptic the *passivum divinum* points to God. This is the chapter's deepest comfort. The dragon's beast does not seize his reign; it is granted. The forty-two months are not random; they are measured. The war on the saints is not outside God's sovereignty; it is within His permission and bounded by His clock. As Calvin saw consistently in Daniel and Revelation: tyrants rage only on a leash."
